00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:55,000
That is...

459
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,000
Structural insight.

460
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:01,000
If you cast a divination spell or identity-like effect,

461
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:04,000
you get advantage on associated arcana checks,

462
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:10,000
and you can ask one additional structural question about the system sustaining the magic.

463
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:14,000
And red line reality.

464
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:17,000
When a creature succeeds on a saving throw against your spell

465
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:21,000
or a magical effect attempts to bind, categorize, or relocate you,

466
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:26,000
you can force a reroll or reduce the effect to partial.

467
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,000
It's the best fucking pen in the world.

468
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:31,000
And the air will smell like heated ink when this occurs,

469
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:34,000
because you got straight fire going through that quill.

470
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:36,000
That's insane.

471
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,000
That is so...

472
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,000
Damn.

473
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,000
That's a good list of shit, and I love it.

474
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:45,000
And for all of us, you'll notice each hilt,

475
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:48,000
and I think it was more clear on yours, Bizard,

476
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:52,000
but there's this faint metallic thread.

477
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:54,000
And that's for all of us.

478
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:58,000
We all have that, and when we are all together with these items

479
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,000
within 20 feet of each other,

480
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:05,000
we will gain advantage on a saving throw against force movement,

481
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:10,000
planar displacement, or magical classification effects.

482
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:12,000
So we're better together and stronger together,

483
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:14,000
just like we know that we are.

484
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:17,000
Earth!

485
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:19,000
By our powers, come by!

486
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:21,000
I mean, I must be fire.

487
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:23,000
Of course. Wind.

488
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:25,000
Wait, no, it's air?

489
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:27,000
What's the magic?

490
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,000
Air.

491
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,000
Air?

492
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:35,000
I also made myself a dope item called Load Bearer's Edge.

493
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:38,000
This is a rapier,

494
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:42,000
and it is forged in a shoethrous heat

495
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:47,000
using interlocking micro-lattices layered through the steel.

496
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:50,000
So this blade was not made to cut flesh.

497
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:53,000
It was made to find fracture.

498
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,000
So I get some pluses,

499
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:58,000
and it has a structural stress reader.

500
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:01,000
So when I hit a creature that is adjacent to a wall, pillar,

501
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:04,000
large object, or architectural structure,

502
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:08,000
or inside a magical construct, barrier, ward, or rune circle,

503
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:10,000
I get extra damage.

504
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:13,000
And this is so cool.

505
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,000
I'm reading this as I go, Russ, and it's blowing my mind.

506
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Anchor the fracture.

507
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:21,000
When a structure, portal, or magical boundary within 15 feet

508
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:24,000
shifts, collapses, or destabilizes,

509
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:27,000
you may stabilize it until the end of your next turn.

510
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:30,000
So it can delay force teleportation, structural collapse,

511
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:33,000
or magical displacement of the structure.

512
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,000
So sick.

513
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:35,000
Baller.

514
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:37,000
I also have some forge instinct,

515
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:39,000
my stone's wisdom,

516
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:44,000
where I can know about things just because of my innate knowledge.

517
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:48,000
So with this and the potions that we got

518
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:53,000
from those, the major and minor,

519
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:57,000
and the sweet apothecary, I feel like we have...

520
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:58,000
We're going to kick some ass.

521
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,000
Yes.

522
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:00,000
Absolutely.

523
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,000
Or read books.

524
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:02,000
I'm not...

525
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:04,000
Well, you have to do both.

526
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:05,000
Yeah.

527
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:07,000
Studies don't stop just because we're on the road.

528
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,000
That's right.

529
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:10,000
Well, then are we getting a wagon?

530
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:13,000
Honestly, if we're going to bring Alistair,

531
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:15,000
we might want to bring a wagon.

532
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:17,000
I'm pretty sure we can secure something.

533
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,000
I don't want to carry him.

534
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,000
Please, Magic Daddy, can we get a wagon?

535
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,000
Yes.

536
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:24,000
Yes, we can get a wagon.

537
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:26,000
Yes.

538
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:30,000
We hear, as we fade from this scene,

539
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:33,000
we hear the sound of...

540
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,000
Coconuts?

541
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:35,000
A slightly...

542
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:37,000
Why would a wagon have coconuts?

543
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:40,000
I don't know, because I thought maybe it was a horse.

544
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:42,000
Exactly.

545
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:44,000
Just the way you put your hands together

546
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:46,000
is like, coconuts, I get it.

547
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,000
You got it, yeah.

548
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:52,000
We hear the sound of just one slightly squeaky wheel

549
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:56,000
as we see Alistair being pulled in this wagon

550
00:35:56,000 --> 00:36:01,000
and the four of you heading off into the Verboten forest.

